t%20easier%20to%20maintain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-right-way-to-set-boundaries-with-people-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthy%20boundaries%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20cutting%20down%20on%20negative%20interactions%2C%20it%20allows%20people%20%26quot%3Bto%20enjoy%20the%20more%20pleasant%20moments%2C%26quot%3B%20Davis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20tend%20to%20get%20into%20long%2C%20one-sided%20phone%20conversations%20with%20a%20parent%2C%20setting%20a%20shorter%20timeframe%20for%20calls%20can%20help.%20By%20giving%20yourself%20an%20out%20after%2030%20minutes%2C%20you%20can%20avoid%20feeling%20as%20exhausted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20pulling%20away%20can%20change%20the%20dynamics%20of%20the%20relationship%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20some%20parents%20yearn%20more%20for%20that%20connection%20with%20their%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20Davis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Wright%20says%20this%20has%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Brare%26quot%3B%20occurrence%20in%20her%20practice%2C%20some%20of%20her%20clients%20reported%20that%20their%20relationships%20improved%20after%20they%20went%20low-contact.%20Some%20parents%20ended%20up%20going%20to%20therapy%20or%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-estranged-mother-daughter-reconnected-after-no-contact-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereconnect%20with%20their%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20seen%20really%20beautiful%20relational%20shifts%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%20%26quot%3BHere's%20a%20parent%20willing%20to%20do%20the%20hard%20work%20and%20show%20up%20for%20the%20relationship.%26quot%3B%20In%20those%20instances%2C%20low%20contact%20was%20only%20a%20temporary%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-time-to-go-low-contact-with-parent-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731620322000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6735303d192f5258985850a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-time-to-go-low-contact-with-parent-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Unlike%20going%20no-contact%2C%20a%20low-contact%20relationship%20allows%20you%20to%20set%20boundaries%20and%20reduce%20communication%20without%20becoming%20fully%20estranged.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpugachevsky%40businessinsider.com%20(Julia%20Pugachevsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-time-to-go-low-contact-with-parent-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bob's%20Red%20Mill%20is%20owned%20by%20its%20700%20employees.%20Its%20CEO%20says%20that%20is%20key%20to%20its%20success.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Workers%20at%20Bob's%20Red%20Mill%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6734645c88cea3ba1c205219%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221133%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBob's%20Red%20Mill%20became%20fully%20employee-owned%20in%202020.%3Cp%3EBob's%20Red%20Mill%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBob's%20Red%20Mill%20became%20employee-owned%20in%202020%20with%20an%20Employee%20Stock%20Ownership%20Program%20or%20ESOP.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECEO%20Trey%20Winthrop%20said%20when%20founder%20Bob%20Moore%20died%2C%20the%20ESOP%20helped%20with%20the%20transition.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWinthrop%20said%20being%20employee-owned%20boosts%20employee%20engagement%20and%20makes%20his%20job%20easier.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%2094-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbob-moore-bobs-red-mill-founder-employee-owned-company-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBob%20Moore%3C%2Fa%3E%20died%20in%20February%2C%20Bob's%20Red%20Mill%20not%20only%20lost%20its%20founder%20but%20also%20the%20face%20of%20the%20company%2C%20literally%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20on%20every%20package.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%202010%2C%20the%20natural%20foods%20company%20initiated%20a%20process%20that%20would%20help%20prepare%20it%20for%20Moore's%20eventual%20passing.%20Moore%2C%20who%20founded%20the%20whole-grain%20food%20company%20in%201978%20and%20turned%20it%20into%20a%20global%20empire%2C%20decided%20to%20transfer%20ownership%20to%20its%20more%20than%20700%20employees.%20By%202020%2C%20Bob's%20Red%20Mill%20was%20entirely%20employee-owned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20becoming%20100%25%20employee-owned%2C%20we%20knew%20that%20when%20Bob%20passed%20that%20we%20would%20control%20our%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Trey%20Winthrop%2C%20the%20company's%20CEO%20since%202022%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20have%20to%20think%20about%20external%20problems.%20I%20got%20to%20focus%20internally%20on%20all%20the%20people%20here%20and%20how%20we%20were%20going%20to%20grieve%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%20said%20he%20frequently%20fended%20off%20large%20corporations%20that%20wanted%20to%20buy%20them%20out.%20But%20because%20of%20the%20employee-ownership%20program%2C%20Winthrop%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20at%20Bob's%20Red%20Mill%20for%2017%20years%2C%20said%20he%20did%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20an%20external%20threat%20coming%20in%20and%20trying%20to%20buy%20up%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBob's%20Red%20Mill%20is%20one%20of%20about%206%2C500%20American%20companies%20that%20operate%20with%20an%20Employee%20Stock%20Ownership%20Plan%2C%20or%20ESOP%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nceo.org%2Farticles%2Femployee-ownership-by-the-numbers%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEmployee%2520Stock%2520Ownership-%2CHow%2520Many%2520ESOPs%2520Are%2520There%253F%2Cassets%2520of%2520over%2520%25242.1%2520trillion.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENational%20Center%20for%20Employee%20Ownership%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(NCEO).%20The%20largest%20majority%20employee-owned%20company%20in%20the%20US%20as%20of%20November%20is%20Publix%2C%20a%20Florida-based%20supermarket%20chain%20with%20more%20than%20225%2C000%20employees%2C%20according%20to%20the%20NCEO.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20smiling%20in%20suit%20jacket%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6734766c5ec9bfa3d63dba4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBob's%20Red%20Mill%20CEO%20Trey%20Winthrop%20said%20the%20ESOP%20boosts%20employee%20engagement.%3Cp%3EBob's%20Red%20Mill%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20ESOP%20is%20formed%2C%20ownership%20shares%20are%20distributed%20to%20employees%2C%20giving%20them%20a%20financial%20stake%20in%20the%20success%20of%20the%20company.%20When%20an%20employee%20retires%2C%20the%20company%20buys%20back%20those%20shares%20at%20market%20price%20within%20a%20set%20number%20of%20years.%20ESOPs%2C%20which%20are%20technically%20retirement%20plans%2C%20are%20governed%20by%20some%20of%20the%20same%20laws%20that%20apply%20to%20401(k)%20plans%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.esopassociation.org%2Fwhat-is-an-esop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20ESOP%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20financial%20equity%20is%20important%2C%20Winthrop%20said%20it's%20not%20really%20the%20reason%20people%20join%20ESOPs%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20real%20benefit%20comes%20from%20how%20being%20employee-owned%20impacts%20the%20company%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20own%20our%20jobs.%20We%20don't%20rent%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20calling%20it%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Bguiding%20principle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f0e4967-61a2-478a-a33a-27994ffb7976%5C%22%3EESOPs%20boost%20employee%20engagement%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20hefty%20payouts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWinthrop%2C%20who%20was%20at%20Bob's%20Red%20Mill%20long%20before%20the%20ESOP%2C%20said%20being%20employee-owned%20boosts%20employee%20engagement%20and%20retention.%20He%20said%20it%20creates%20a%20two-way%20street%20of%20communication%2C%20where%20the%20company%20can%20share%20financials%20with%20employees%20and%20workers%20are%20given%20a%20voice%2C%20in%20part%20through%20being%20active%20in%20committees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20getting%20people%20engaged%20culturally%20so%20they%20understand%20what%20success%20is%2C%20and%20then%20getting%20them%20juiced%20about%20that%20equity%20once%20they%20understand%20how%20they%20can%20grow%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20CEO%2C%20Winthrop%20said%20he%20thinks%20being%20employee-owned%20actually%20makes%20his%20job%20easier%20as%20it%20creates%20a%20higher%20level%20of%20trust%20between%20him%20and%20other%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20an%20ESOP%20does%20not%20prevent%20a%20company%20from%20being%20sold.%20But%20it%20can%20ensure%20that%20if%20the%20board%20does%20choose%20to%20sell%20it%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20employees%20will%20share%20in%20the%20profits%2C%20Winthrop%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Clif%20Bar%20sold%20to%20food%20giant%20Mondelez%20for%20%242.9%20billion%20in%202022%2C%20the%20company%20was%2020%25%20employee-owned%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20%24580%20million%20shared%20among%201%2C300%20people%20%E2%80%94%20an%20average%20payout%20of%20%24488%2C000%20per%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20rather%20than%20think%20of%20an%20ESOP%20as%20a%20retirement%20tool%2C%20Winthrop%20said%20it's%20better%20thought%20of%20as%20an%20employee%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eengagement%20tool.%20Still%2C%20he%20said%20it%20might%20not%20be%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20trying%20to%20maximize%20your%20price%20when%20you're%20selling%20your%20company%2C%20an%20ESOP%20doesn't%20always%20pay%20top%20dollar%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20but%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20have%20employees%20that%20you%20believe%20in%20and%20you%20want%20them%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20financial%20success%20of%20their%20work%20and%20promote%20the%20middle%20class%2C%20then%20you%20should%20heavily%20look%20at%20being%20an%20ESOP.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20news%20tip%20or%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbobs-red-mill-ceo-employee-owned-esop-benefits-bob-moore-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731620286000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673475e75ec9bfa3d63dba37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbobs-red-mill-ceo-employee-owned-esop-benefits-bob-moore-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bob's%20Red%20Mill%20CEO%20Trey%20Winthrop%20said%20being%20employee-owned%2C%20with%20an%20ESOP%2C%20boosts%20employee%20engagement%20and%20helped%20transition%20after%20Bob%20Moore's%20death.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40businessinsider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbobs-red-mill-ceo-employee-owned-esop-benefits-bob-moore-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20picks%20Robert%20F%20Kennedy%20Jr%20to%20lead%20department%20of%20health%20and%20human%20services%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731620165000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-115313092%2Cimgsize-1200317.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-picks-robe