aigns%20reveals%20some%20striking%20differences%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20passage%20of%20time%2C%20Trump's%20appeal%20remained%20consistent%20across%20both%20elections.%20His%20support%20base%20remained%20loyal%2C%20and%20he%20continued%20to%20draw%20significant%20support%20from%20key%20demographic%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20CNN%20exit%20poll%2C%20White%20voters%20without%20college%20degrees%20have%20always%20supported%20Trump%20and%20this%20was%20the%20case%20in%202024%20as%20well.%20Latino%20voters%20were%20shifting%20towards%20Trump%20since%202016%2C%20but%20this%20year%2C%20Trump%20won%20them%20in%20full%20glory.%20Votes%20from%20women%20plateaued%20for%20Harris%20as%20compared%20to%20women's%20votes%20for%20Biden%20and%20Clinton%2C%20even%20though%20she%20aimed%20to%20mobilise%20women%20through%20reproductive%20rights%20and%20Trump%20enjoyed%20his%20edge%20among%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20notable%20difference%20between%20the%20two%20elections%20was%20Trump's%20ability%20to%20secure%20a%20popular%20vote%20majority%20in%202024.%20This%20was%20a%20significant%20departure%20from%202016%2C%20where%20he%20lost%20the%20popular%20vote%20to%20Hillary%20Clinton.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20Trump's%20false%20statements%20have%20remained%20consistent%20over%20the%20years.%20His%20comments%20on%20crime%20rates%20and%20poverty%20have%20been%20a%20subject%20of%20debate.%20In%202016%2C%20he%20highlighted%20a%2017%20per%20cent%20increase%20in%20homicides%20in%20the%2050%20largest%20US%20cities%2C%20which%20was%20the%20largest%20increase%20in%2025%20years.%20However%2C%20this%20claim%20cherry-picked%20statistics%20and%20ignored%20the%20overall%20decline%20in%20murders%20during%20the%20Obama%20administration%20and%20preceding%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFast-forward%20to%202024%2C%20Trump%20claimed%20that%20%26quot%3Bour%20crime%20rate%20is%20going%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20according%20to%20the%20FBI's%20preliminary%20analysis%2C%20violent%20crime%20and%20property%20crime%20are%20near%20historic%20lows%20and%20decreased%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%20His%202016%20statement%20on%20Latino%20poverty%20was%20accurate%20in%20raw%20numbers%2C%20stating%20that%20two%20million%20more%20Latinos%20were%20in%20poverty%20since%20Obama%20took%20office.%20However%2C%20he%20omitted%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Latino%20population%20grew%20and%20their%20poverty%20rate%20actually%20decreased.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20selective%20use%20of%20statistics%20has%20raised%20concerns.%20For%20instance%2C%20while%20food%20prices%20have%20increased%20by%2021%20per%20cent%20and%20gas%20prices%20by%2035%20per%20cent%20since%20Biden%20took%20office%2C%20Trump's%20claims%20exaggerate%20these%20numbers.%20He%20mentioned%20a%2057%20per%20cent%20increase%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20groceries%20and%2060%20per%20cent%20increase%20in%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20election%20also%20highlighted%20the%20ongoing%20issues%20with%20polling%20accuracy.%20Despite%20efforts%20to%20improve%20polling%20techniques%2C%20Trump's%20support%20was%20consistently%20underestimated%20during%20both%20the%20years%20-%202016%20and%202024.%20Hilary%20Clinton%20and%20Kamala%20Harris%20had%20both%20headed%20into%20Election%20Day%20asserting%20that%20they%20would%20defeat%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20voter%20phenomenon%20has%20left%20many%20scratching%20their%20heads%2C%20and%20two%20key%20theories%20attempt%20to%20explain%20why%20polling%20predictions%20often%20miss%20the%20mark.%20Firstly%2C%20Trump%20supporters%20tend%20to%20be%20anti-establishment%20and%20wary%20of%20authority%2C%20which%20may%20lead%20them%20to%20systematically%20refuse%20pollsters'%20calls%2C%20essentially%20staying%20under%20the%20radar.%20This%20reluctance%20to%20engage%20with%20pollsters%20could%20be%20due%20to%20a%20sense%20of%20mistrust%20or%20a%20desire%20to%20keep%20their%20opinions%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20some%20hypothesise%20that%20the%20criteria%20pollsters%20use%20to%20identify%20%26quot%3Blikely%26quot%3B%20voters%20inadvertently%20screens%20out%20individuals%20inclined%20to%20support%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BBradley%20effect%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BWilder%20effect%26quot%3B%20offers%20insight%20into%20this%20phenomenon%2C%20where%20voters%20conceal%20their%20true%20preferences%20due%20to%20social%20desirability%20bias%2C%20particularly%20when%20faced%20with%20questions%20about%20racial%20or%20sensitive%20topics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20similarities%20between%20the%202016%20and%202024%20elections%20suggest%20that%20American%20politics%20has%20become%20increasingly%20polarised.%20The%20country%20is%20largely%20divided%20between%20two%20equal-sized%20coalitions%2C%20resulting%20in%20Groundhog%20Day-style%20repeat%20elections.%20This%20polarisation%20has%20significant%20implications%20for%20the%20future%20of%20American%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Barack%20Obama's%20win%20in%202008%2C%20the%20country%20was%20positive%20about%20heading%20in%20the%20right%20direction%2C%20fair%2C%20even-handed%20and%20unbiased.%20However%2C%20after%20two%20disastrous%20losses%20of%202016%20and%202024%2C%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20shirk%20off%20the%20thought%20that%20the%20losses%20might%20just%20be%20related%20to%20the%20candidates'%20identities%20since%20one%20of%20the%20common%20denominators%20between%20both%20the%20elections%20are%20that%20the%20Democratic%20contenders%20were%20both%20women.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731603840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fdmlqqgeo_donald-trump_625x300_10_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdeja-vu-trumps-2024-victory-follows-2016-script-7020796%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump's%202024%20victory%20is%20very%20reminiscent%20of%20his%202016%20one.%20However%2C%20comparing%20Trump's%202016%20and%202024%20presiden